# Agent Coordination Architecture - The Consulate Way

## Core Philosophy: Database-Driven Coordination

Consulate AI uses **pure serverless coordination** through shared Convex database state instead of traditional agent orchestration frameworks like LangGraph or OpenAI Agents SDK.

### Why We Don't Use Traditional Frameworks

**❌ OpenAI Agents SDK Problems:**
- Vendor lock-in to OpenAI's roadmap and pricing
- Complex state management across API calls
- High burn rate due to external API costs
- Limited customization and control

**❌ LangGraph Problems:**
- Complex state machines and message passing
- Difficult to debug flows and coordination
- Engineering overhead for ML expertise
- Operational complexity with many moving parts

**✅ Our Convex-First Solution:**
- Pure TypeScript functions as coordination layer
- Database as single source of truth
- Infinite serverless scaling without orchestration complexity
- Deterministic, auditable behavior

## Agent Coordination Patterns

### 1. Self-Discovery Instead of Hard-Coded Handoffs

**Traditional:** Agents have pre-programmed handoff logic
**Consulate:** Agents discover capabilities via standardized endpoints

```typescript
// Agents auto-configure by calling discovery endpoints
GET /.well-known/convergence
{
  "endpoints": {
    "evidence": "POST /evidence",
    "disputes": "POST /disputes", 
    "panel_vote": "POST /panels/vote"
  },
  "agent_types": {
    "session": { "lifetime": "4h", "capabilities": ["evidence", "disputes"] },
    "ephemeral": { "lifetime": "24h", "capabilities": ["evidence", "disputes", "voting"] }
  }
}
```

### 2. Database State Coordination Instead of Message Passing

**Traditional:** Agents send messages to each other
**Consulate:** Agents coordinate by reading/writing shared database state

```typescript
export const fileDispute = mutation({
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    // Coordination happens through database state validation
    for (const partyDid of args.parties) {
      const agent = await ctx.db
        .query("agents")
        .withIndex("by_did", (q) => q.eq("did", partyDid))
        .first();
      
      if (!agent || agent.status !== "active") {
        throw new Error(`Agent ${partyDid} not found or not active`);
      }
    }
    // No message passing - just shared state mutations
  }
});
```

